# GitHub Pages deploy verification

Production and preview use **legacy GitHub Pages** (`build_type: legacy`). Builds take **1â€“6 minutes** after `git push`. The live URL may still serve the old `APP_VERSION` while `status=building`.

**Do not** add `.github/workflows/deploy-github-pages.yml` or switch to `build_type: workflow` â€” that reintroduces conflicts with GitHub's built-in `pages-build-deployment` workflow.

## After every push to `origin/main` and/or `preview`

Run and **do not tell the user deploy is complete** until this passes:

```bash
npm run deploy:verify
```

Or full push + automatic recovery + verify from `dev`:

```bash
npm run deploy
```

`npm run deploy` and `deploy:verify` **automatically run `pages-recovery`** when a wedged legacy Pages build is detected (stale `github-pages` deployments blocking `pages-build-deployment`).

## URLs

- Production: https://bnarcum.github.io/cisco-portfolio-navigator/cisco-portfolio-navigator.html
- Preview: https://bnarcum.github.io/cisco-portfolio-navigator-preview/cisco-portfolio-navigator.html

## If verification times out

1. Check live vs expected version:
   ```bash
   curl -sS "https://bnarcum.github.io/cisco-portfolio-navigator/cisco-portfolio-navigator.html?cb=$RANDOM" | rg -o '__CPN_BUILD="[^"]+"'
   gh api repos/bnarcum/cisco-portfolio-navigator/pages --jq '{status, build_type}'
   gh api "repos/bnarcum/cisco-portfolio-navigator/pages/builds?per_page=2" --jq '.[] | {status, commit: .commit[0:7], error: .error.message}'
   ```

2. If `pages-build-deployment` failed with **"in progress deployment"** or legacy build is stuck `building`/`errored`, run **wedged deployment recovery** below.

3. Report timeout, last live version, and Pages settings link. Suggest hard refresh (Cmd+Shift+R). Do not claim deploy is complete until live HTML serves expected `__CPN_BUILD`.

## Wedged deployment recovery (production)

**Root cause:** `pages-build-deployment` uses `actions/deploy-pages`, which registers `github-pages` environment deployments. Stale SUCCESS or piled-up FAILURE nodes block new deploys (*"cancel â€¦ first"*), wedging legacy builds in `building`/`errored`.

**Automatic (preferred):**

```bash
npm run deploy:recover
npm run deploy:verify
```

**Manual (if gh automation unavailable):**

Symptoms:
- `pages-build-deployment` fails: `Deployment request failed â€¦ due to in progress deployment`
- Legacy build stuck `building` with `duration: 0`, or Pages `status: errored`
- Preview updates but production stays on older `__CPN_BUILD`

```bash
# 1) List recent github-pages deployments
gh api graphql -f query='query { repository(owner:"bnarcum", name:"cisco-portfolio-navigator") { deployments(first:8, environments:["github-pages"], orderBy:{field:CREATED_AT, direction:DESC}) { nodes { id commitOid latestStatus { state } } } } }' \
  --jq '.data.repository.deployments.nodes[] | {id, oid: .commitOid[0:7], state: .latestStatus.state}'

# 2) Delete wedged FAILURE deployment nodes (use id from step 1)
gh api graphql -f query='mutation { deleteDeployment(input:{id:"<DEPLOYMENT_ID>"}) { clientMutationId } }'

# 3) Reaffirm legacy-only Pages
gh api -X PUT repos/bnarcum/cisco-portfolio-navigator/pages \
  -f build_type=legacy -f 'source[branch]=main' -f 'source[path]=/'

# 4) Queue fresh legacy build
gh api -X POST repos/bnarcum/cisco-portfolio-navigator/pages/builds

# 5) Poll until production serves expected version
npm run deploy:verify
```

**Do not** manually `POST pages/builds` repeatedly while Actions deploys are failing â€” clear wedged deployments first.

If recovery fails after ~6 minutes: https://github.com/bnarcum/cisco-portfolio-navigator/settings/pages
